Nigeria’s COVID-19 total crossed the 91,000 mark on Monday night with 1,204 new cases reported from across the country, according to the latest update by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). The NCDC update, gathered from 20 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), reveals that Lagos recorded 654 new cases, which is the highest for the day; FCT – 200, Plateau – 60, Kaduna – 54 and Kano – 40 to make the top five states with the highest number of new cases for the day. The update also revealed that 655 persons were discharged after they recovered from the virus, taking the total number of recoveries from across the country to 75,699 while seven deaths were recorded on the day, taking Nigeria’s COVID-19 death toll to 1,318. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The breakdown of the latest update is as follows: Lagos-654 NBA: Stephen Curry Scores Career-High Points Total In Golden State Warriors Win Liverpool Will Buy In January If It Is ‘Right Thing’, Says Klopp FCT-200 Plateau-60 Kaduna-54 Kano-40 Rivers-30 Edo-28 Nasarawa-25 Kebbi-19 Bauchi-18 Oyo-13 Akwa Ibom-12 Bayelsa-11 Ogun-11 Delta-9 Abia-8 Benue-5 Imo-3 Borno-2 Sokoto-1 Osun-1 91,351 confirmed 75,699 discharged 1,318 deaths SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION